About this hotel

Set on lush grounds, this understated hotel is 4 km from Majorelle Garden, 2 km from Koutoubia Mosque, and 3 km from both Bahia Palace and the buzzing Jemaa el-Fnaa square.

Check-in time: 3:00 PM
Check-out time: 12:00 PM

    I was informed that money exchange rates occur two times a day at the hotel; morning and evening. The rates at the hotels basically remained the same same during my two weeks in Morocco; $1.00 USD = 9.70 Dirhams. The bank rate was higher, $1.00 USD= 9.99 Dirhams.
    On May 8th in the early evening my sister exchanged $98.00 USD. She was given an exchange rate of 9.10 Dirhams with no receipt. I called the front desk and questioned the individual (don't have his name) about the rate and he stated that was the evening rate and he would give the money back if we disagreed. I told him I was on my way to the front desk. Before I could make it downstairs, he was knocking at the door. He returned the $98.00 and he was given the 891.45 dirhams.

    I previously stayed here two times nearly three years ago, and was very pleased in late 2019 to find the property upgraded. The hallways and public spaces look nicer, the rooms and furnishings are updated, and the service overall was clearly better. I also enjoyed the breakfast, a large buffet with more interesting selections and seemingly more authentic Moroccan items than before. Overall the property seems a much nicer experience. Also it's good to see the renovated bathrooms featuring quality Moroccan amenities made with Argan.
    Despite Marriott's have eviscerated the beloved SPG program there really are a number of great touches here to please the elite members: a welcome letter from the GM, an enormous complimentary bottle of mineral water plus several little bottles, fresh flowers, a fruit plate, a plate of confections delivered mid-afternoon, a thoughtful holiday gift, the GM's cocktail reception, and so on.
    And I was reminded during my two visits here this year how nice and tranquil it is off-season; you can sit outside your room if you're on the ground floor and listen to the birds chirping. Or sit poolside (also renovated and improved!) and relax for hours.
    Adding the convenience of Le Méridien's location it made my repeat visits all the more worthwhile. I've stayed at a lot of SPG/Marriott properties in Africa and Asia, and this property still remains one of the best value use of Marriott points anywhere, especially given this level of hospitality. Plus I remembered how scuffed the hallways were and how frayed the carpets and furnishings used to be; it's clear the hotel definitely upped their game since my prior visits!

    Reception was not very friendly specially the short hair woman was treated me at the money change like I owe her something at the check in. I thought I’m going to give them one star but other staff was good my bad feeling faded away.
    After checking out they ordered a taxi for us. Bell boy told us taxi fare is 100 dirams. Usual fare should be 50. It seems like the hotel is fixing the taxi fare from its own gusts. Poor decision in my opinion. If you need a taxi don’t let them to do it for you. Taxis are always parked just outside the hotel gate. Just go out and get a taxi it’ll cost you 50 dirams to go to city. Ask the driver first.

    Hivernage

    Refined, modern Hivernage is known for nightlife, with a casino, cocktail lounges, hotel dance clubs and chic global restaurants with live music. The Royal Theatre, with domes and Ancient Egyptian–style columns, stages concerts in an amphitheater. Nearby, the Menara Gardens, with a huge reflecting pool and mountains in the background, date to the 12th century, and El-Harti Park has fountains and a rose garden.

    About this hotel

    Set on lush grounds, this understated hotel is 4 km from Majorelle Garden, 2 km from Koutoubia Mosque, and 3 km from both Bahia Palace and the buzzing Jemaa el-Fnaa square. …

    Casual rooms and suites with tile floors provide Wi-Fi access, satellite TV and safes, as well as en suite bathrooms. Some have sitting areas and/or terraces. Room service is available 24/7.

    Amenities include 4 restaurants, a gym and 2 outdoor pools (1 for kids). There's also a tennis court, a spa with a hammam, and meeting and event space. Breakfast is available.
